<HEAD>Red Cross DC-3 Crashes On Mercy Flight To Mozambique</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HARARE, Zimbabwe (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Red Cross DC-3 transport plane
carrying relief supplies for Mozambique crashed on a farm near
Harare, injuring all three people aboard, police said today.
   The white DC-3 plowed through trees on the farm at Epworth
outside Harare on Tuesday.
   Police said one of the plane's two engines failed and the pilot
was looking for a place for an emergency landing when the aircraft
crashed.
   The three crew members who were injured and rushed to hospital
were not immediately identified.
   The Red Cross and other relief agencies often launch flights
containing food relief from Zimbabwe into Mozambique, its eastern
neighbor. Hundreds of thousands of Mozambicans face starvation as a
result of drought and civil war.
