<HEAD>Poll Finds Presidential Race A Dead Heat in Maryland</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BALTIMORE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Democrat Michael Dukakis and Republican George
Bush are in a virtual dead heat in predominantly Democratic
Maryland, according to a poll released Wednesday by WBAL-TV.
   Dukakis had 47.6 percent and Bush had 47.4 percent, with 5
percent undecided in the latest Maryland poll.
   Since the poll has a margin of error of plus or minus 3 points,
the results indicate the race in Maryland would be a toss-up.
   The survey of 638 state residents considered likely to vote in
November was conducted Sept. 8-11 by Western Maryland College
political science professor Herbert C. Smith for WBAL.
