<HEAD>Chrysler Announces Jeep Expansions In Toledo, Canada</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOLEDO, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Chrysler Motors Corp. announced a $24
million plan Wednesday to increase Jeep vehicle production at its
Toledo and Brampton, Ontario, assembly plants in January.
   Richard Dauch, executive vice president of manufacturing, said
the increase will result in production of 23,000 more vehicles a
year at the Toledo assembly plant. Production at the Brampton plant
in Canada will increase 32,000 a year, Dauch said.
   The two plants combined ultimately could produce more than
403,000 Jeep vehicles a year if warranted by market demand.
