<FILEID>AP-NR-09-21-88 2028EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Northrop     09-21 0162</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Northrop,0169</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Northrop Adopts `Poison Pill' Takeover Defense; No Offer Expected</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Northrop Corp. on Wednesday announced it had
adopted a ``poison pill'' defense against hostile takeover
attempts, although it is not aware of any potential suitors.
   In the event of a hostile takeover move, the plan would allow
Northrop shareholders to buy additional Northrop stock or stock in
the potential buyer at a 50 percent discount.
   Such plans, in common use for several years, are called poison
pills because they dilute the value of a potential buyer's
holdings, thus making the target company harder to swallow.
   ``The board noted that the action was not taken in response to
any acquisition attempt, and the board is not aware of any effort
to acquire control of Northrop,'' according to a news release by
the aerospace and electronics company.
   Rather, the board considered such a plan prudent because of a
spate of corporate takeovers in recent years, the company said.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> AP880921-0260 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-09-21-88 2039EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>d f AM-Hurricane-Hyatt     09-21 0180</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Hurricane-Hyatt,0189</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Hotel Company Announces Closings Due To Gilbert</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hyatt International Corp. announced Wednesday it
is temporarily closing its two hotels in Cancun because of
devastation wreaked by Hurricane Gilbert on Mexico's Yucatan
Peninsula.
   The Hyatt Regency Cancun and Hyatt Cancun Caribe will close
immediately, the hotel company said in a statement.
   Rainer Mohaupt, Hyatt's regional vice president for Latin
America, said Hyatt would implement comprehensive rebuilding plans
as soon as possible.
   Mohaupt said all guests registered at either of the hotels and
in residence during the hurricane would be invited back to Cancun
and provided with complimentary rooms to finish their interrupted
vacations.
   The invitations would be good for the period April 15, 1989,
through Dec. 15, 1989.
   Mohaupt also said guests holding future reservations with Hyatt
at either of the Cancun hotels would be given assistance for
rescheduling their vacations to Acapulco at a 25 percent discount
from Cancun prices.
   He said arrangements also could be made for alternative
accomodations at other Hyatt resort destinations, including Key
West, Grand Cayman, Puerto Rico or Hawaii.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
